    "recap_headline": "University of Minnesota Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BLOOMINGTON, IND. \u2013\nThe University of Minnesota baseball team opened up their three game road series against Indiana University tonight, seeing all nine starters reach base safely but falling to the Hoosiers 8-6 at Bart Kaufman Field.\nJoe Sperry\ncame out of the bullpen for Minnesota and was credited with the loss.\nLuke Ryerse\nwas a bright spot for the Gophers, coming out of the bullpen as well and throwing 3.2 scoreless innings with three strikeouts.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Gophers got on the board immediately, jumping out to an early lead in the top of the first inning.\nTy Allen\ngot things going by splitting the infield with an RBI single up the middle to score the first run of the tilt.\nDavis Hamilton\nquickly followed it up by tallying two RBIs on a double out to left field. An RBI groundout from\nMichael Lippe\ncapped off a four run inning for Minnesota.\nThe Hoosiers gained some ground, narrowing the lead to 4-2 before the Gophers expanded their advantage in the second. A two out, two run home run to straight away center field off the bat of\nCharlie Sutherland\nbrought the score to 6-2 in favor of Minnesota heading into the third.\nThe Gophers were unable to hold the lead, as Indiana scored six runs throughout the third and fifth innings to grab game one at 8-6.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Every Gopher starter reached base safely in the loss.\n\u00bb Minnesota's highest scoring inning was the first, when it pushed four runs across.\n\u00bb Minnesota pitchers faced 39 Indiana hitters in the game, allowing eight ground balls and seven fly balls while striking out eight.\n\u00bb The Gophers drew six walks from Indiana pitching.\n\u00bb Sutherland led the Gophers at the plate, going 1 for 4 with a home run and two RBIs.",
